
================================================================================
TYPES OF RICE 
================================================================================

TYPE            GRAIN LENGTH                FLAVOR                  TEXTURE 
white rice      short, medium, long         mild, neutral           fluffy (long-grain), sticky (short-grain) 
used in stir-fries, pilafs, sushi (short-grain), rice pudding, misc side dishes
polished grain, lower in fiber and nutrients

brown rice      short, medium, long         nutty, earthy           chewy, firm 
used in healthy bowls, salads, stir fries. 
whole grain is higher in fiber so it takes longer to cook 

basmati rice    long                        aromatic, nutty         light, fluffy, non-sticky 
used in indian cuisine (biryani, pilaf), middle eastern dishes 
rinse before cooking to remove excess starch 

jasmine rice    long                        floral, slightly sweet  soft, slightly sticky 
used in thai and southeast asian dishes
best steamed or cooked via absorption method 

arborio rice    short                       mild, creamy            high starch, creamy when cooked 
used in risotto, rice pudding
requires constant stirring and gradual liquid addition 

sushi rice      short                       mild, slightly sweet    sticky 
used in sushi, onigiri 
season with rice vinegar, sugar, and salt 

wild rice       not actually a rice         earthy, nutty           chewy 
used in salads, stuffing, pilafs 
longer cooking time, often blended with other rice 

black rice      medium, long                rich, nutty             chewy 
used in salads, desserts, asian dishes 
high in antioxidants (anthocyanins) 

red rice        medium                      earthy, robust          chewy 
used in health focused dishes, grain bowls 
whole grain, high in fiber and nutrients 

sticky rice     short                       mild                    very sticky 
used in asian desserts, dim sum, thai sticky rice 
despite the name it's gluten free 

parboiled rice  long                        neutral                 firm, separate grains 
steamed before milling, retains more nutrients 

instant rice    varies                      mild                    soft, sometimes mushy 
uesd in quick meals, camping
it's pre-cooked and dehydrated, so it's less flavorful


================================================================================
GRAIN LENGTH 
================================================================================

short grain tends to be sticky and plump
medium grain tends to be tender and moist
long grain tends to be fluffy and separate when cooked


================================================================================
COOKING METHODS
================================================================================

METHOD              BEST FOR                        NOTES 
boiling             long-grain, wild rice           simple, drain excess water 
steaming            sticky, jasmine, basmati        preserves aroma and texture 
absorption          most types                      water is fully absorbed 
pilaf               long-grain, basmati             sauteed in far before simmering 
risotto             arborio, carnaroli              stirred slowly with broth 
rice cooker         all types                       consistent, hands-off approach 
pressure cooker     brown, wild rice                fast and efficient 

================================================================================
FLAVORINGS & PAIRINGS 
================================================================================

seasonings: 
    salt, herbs, spices, stock, coconut milk 
add-ins: 
    vegetables, meats, seafood, legumes 


================================================================================

it's worth noting that white rice will store for 4-5 years, but brown rice will last 6 months due to oils in the bran 
